                <note rend="inline" type="source">875.01/261: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Albania</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tirana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-01-25T09:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 25, 1925—9 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received January 26—3:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>6. Referring to your January 23 [<hi rend="italic">22</hi>], 1 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >3</hi>] p.m., number 3. Assembly gave vote of confidence 19th. Only
                    British, Greek and Bulgarian representatives having [<hi rend="italic"
                    >have</hi>] replied to formal notification. French colleague requesting
                    instructions. Italian Minister left on extended leave of absence 18th. Republic
                    proclaimed 21st. All but American representative sent acknowledgment in reply to
                    official notification. Italian Chargé d’Affaires asserts his was noncommittal.
                    Ahmet Bey down with influenza. Will [omission] additional assurances as soon as
                    possible. Copy to European Information Center.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grant-Smith</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
